 First, from triangle $ABO$, $\angle AOB = 180^\circ - \angle BAO - \angle ABO$. Note that $AO$ bisects $\angle BAT$ (to see this, draw radii from $O$ to $AB$ and $AT,$ creating two congruent right triangles), so $\angle BAO = \angle BAT/2$.
